      "content": "I hear you, but it feels like you're saying one side is based on history while the other is just a theory. Isn't it fair to say that Originalism is a legitimate legal framework used by many respected jurists, rather than just something that \"ignores\" context? It seems like you're dismissing a huge part of constitutional law as incorrect.",
